nto Services<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/digital-trends\/magento-order-management-system\/#Wrapping-Up-On-Magento-Order-Management-Systems\" title=\"Wrapping Up On Magento Order Management Systems&nbsp;\">Wrapping Up On Magento Order Management Systems&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What-Is-An-Order-Management-System\"><\/span>What Is An Order Management System?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>An order management system (OMS) is a software system that keeps track of orders, inventory and sales.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Think of it as a centralized system where you can manage the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/digital-trends\/business-life-cycle-stages\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">life cycle<\/a> of your customers\u2019 orders.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>An OMS tracks inventory levels by channels, handles your reverse logistics process, manages customer information and automates your order fulfillment process for smooth and efficient operation.<\/p>\n\n\n    <div class=\"cta-custom-box\">\n                    <span style='color: #008dde;'>Request a free consultation with our certified Magento experts<\/span>\n                <a class=\"arrow-right black\" href=\"\/contact\/\"  rel=\"noopener\">\n            Set Up A Consultation        <\/a>\n    <\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"5-Benefits-Of-Implementing-A-Magento-Order-Management-Software\"><\/span>5 Benefits Of Implementing A Magento Order Management Software<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>From reducing human error to streamlining your picking and packing process, here are the top benefits of implementing an OMS.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Reduce Human Error<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that <a href=\"https:\/\/www.freightwaves.com\/news\/technology\/ecommerce-logistics-remains-a-manual-process\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">55%<\/a> of retailers are still using pen-and-paper manual processes in their logistics operations?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Human error is minimized when you implement automation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>An order management system reduces human error<\/strong> by allowing you to keep a database of customer information including names, shipping addresses and tracking info, so you can easily view order history, track packages and update addresses when needed.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This helps ensure your customer information is always up-to-date and reduces the risk of sending packages to incorrect or outdated addresses.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/manual-process-statistics.png\" alt=\"industry stats graph\" class=\"wp-image-5592\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h3>2. Provide Accurate Reporting<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Without tracking, packages can get lost and quickly lead to upset customers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Packages can get misplaced even with tracking, but the difference is, you\u2019re able to see where they end up and either redirect the item or replace it for your customer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><b>When you implement an order management system, you can keep track of the progress of your orders in real time. <\/b><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This can help you get ahead of shipping issues and ensure your customer satisfaction remains high, leading to loyal consumers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"box-cta -bg -border -narrow lazy colors-inverted\"\n     data-bg=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/Ecommerce-Development-655x230.jpg\">\n\n\t        <a href=\"\/digital-trends\/migrate-magento-1-to-magento-2\/\" class=\"box-cta__wrap\">\n    \n        <div class=\"box-cta__text-wrap\">\n            <div class=\"l-heading-v3\">\n                <div class=\"c-heading -h2\">\n                                            <span class=\"c-heading__pre\">YOU MAY ALSO LIKE<\/span>\n                    \n                                            <div class=\"c-heading__title\">How To Migrate Magento 1 To Magento 2 [A Complete Guide]<\/div>\n                                    <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n\n        <div class=\"box-cta__icon\">\n            <svg class=\"icon icon-lib-icon-arrow-right-big \"  aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#lib-icon-arrow-right-big\"><\/use><\/svg>        <\/div>\n\n            <\/a>\n    \n<\/div>\n\n\n<h3>3. Save Time<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An OMS can help you save time by giving you easy access to information at your fingertips.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It records historical order data, so you can quickly pull customer order history or even use the data to determine sales trends and forecast demand.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. Streamline Your Picking &amp; Packing Process<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that <a href=\"https:\/\/assets.kpmg\/content\/dam\/kpmg\/uk\/pdf\/2020\/01\/annual-retail-survey-2020-final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b>43%<\/b><\/a><b> of consumers choose the next-day delivery option when shopping online?<\/b><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>While cost of delivery is a key factor for many consumers, waiting time also plays a vital role, and customers often want their purchases as quickly as possible.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>An order management system helps you speed up the picking and packing process by identifying the fulfillment center closest to your customer, where the item is available.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once it sends the order information to the chosen fulfillment center, your customer\u2019s product gets picked, packed and delivered in the shortest amount of time possible.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/next-day-delivery-option-statistics.png\" alt=\"industry stats graph\" class=\"wp-image-5593\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h3>5. Prevent Over-stocking &amp; Stockouts<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><span data-contrast=\"auto\">According to an Adobe Analytics <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/blog.adobe.com\/en\/publish\/2021\/11\/09\/adobe-shoppers-have-seen-over-2-billion-out-of-stock-messages-online-october-2021#gs.lodzo3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span data-contrast=\"none\">study<\/span><\/a><span data-contrast=\"auto\">, <\/span><b><span data-contrast=\"auto\">two billion out-of-stock messages were presented online in October 2021 alone.<\/span><\/b><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><b><span data-contrast=\"auto\">Overstocking <\/span><\/b><span data-contrast=\"auto\">can rack up costs without creating profit or cash flow, thanks to dead stock resting on your warehouse shelves.<\/span><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><span data-contrast=\"auto\">On the other hand,<\/span><b><span data-contrast=\"auto\"> stockouts <\/span><\/b><span data-contrast=\"auto\">can damage your brand\u2019s reputation and also cause frustration for your customers who are ready to buy your product.<\/span><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><span data-contrast=\"auto\">Ultimately, both issues can lead to a loss in revenue.<\/span><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><span data-contrast=\"auto\">So how does an order management system help prevent these inventory issues?<\/span><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><span data-contrast=\"auto\">An OMS can provide your business with a centralized view of your inventory, which helps you track and manage your stock levels. <\/span><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><span data-contrast=\"auto\">You\u2019ll get a bird&#8217;s eye view of items that need to be reordered and items that might benefit from sales or promotions to get them moving.<\/span><\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/out-of-stock-statistics.png\" alt=\"industry stats graph\" class=\"wp-image-5594\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Top-Features-To-Look-For-In-A-Magento-Order-Management-System\"><\/span>Top Features To Look For In A Magento Order Management System<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Order management systems aren\u2019t necessarily a one-size-fits-all solution. To choose the best system for your business, look for these top features:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><b>Sales channels: <\/b>Your OMS should receive and gather information from all points of your sale, including your in-store, online and call center. Some systems also support orders from different global regions and multiple currencies.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><b>Sales support: <\/b>Your OMS should update your product availability and information in real time for your customers and your customer service team. This ensures that your business delivers a better experience for your customers while supporting customer exchanges and returns.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><b>Customer database: <\/b>Your OMS should have easy access to customer contact details and order activity, including previous orders. This allows your customer service representatives to accurately search throughout your database when assisting a customer.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><b>Customer tagging: <\/b>Your OMS should allow you to effortlessly tag your customers so you can categorize and keep track of your customer database on the spot. For example, you can tag your customers for customer service follow-ups or tag prioritized groups of VIP or even problematic customers.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><b>Cloud-based: <\/b>A cloud-based OMS can come in handy so you can access information from anywhere, as long as you have an internet connection.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><b>Growth and expansion support:<\/b> Before implementing an OMS, consider both your current and future needs. For example, if you plan for business growth, your OMS should be able meet your operational complexities when the time comes.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><b>Inventory management: <\/b>With an OMS, you get a bird\u2019s eye view of your inventory. This can help you track and manage your stock levels and inventory management algorithms that guide orders to their proper warehouse, while identifying the best shipping options. Make sure the solution you choose includes advanced inventory management features.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"5-Best-Order-Management-Solutions-For-Magento\"><\/span>5 Best Order Management Solutions For Magento<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Magento is a top eCommerce platform that offers numerous features, functionalities and integrations.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When combined with an order management system, <b>your e-store can benefit from increased accuracy, efficiency and customer satisfaction.&nbsp;<\/b><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are five of the top order management solutions you can integrate with Magento:<b>&nbsp;<\/b><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. NetSuite<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While NetSuite isn\u2019t the cheapest solution for order management (it costs between $2,000 and $3,000 monthly), it is a cloud-based ERP and is considered the most full-featured SAAS ERP platform currently available on the market.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is suitable for businesses of all sizes, so whether you\u2019re a start-up or national organization, you can integrate NetSuite with your Magento solution.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>NetSuite doesn\u2019t require hardware, complex set-ups or upfront license and maintenance fees. While it also doesn\u2019t offer a free trial, you can view a <a href=\"https:\/\/6262239.extforms.netsuite.com\/app\/site\/crm\/externalleadpage.nl\/compid.6262239\/.f?formid=12&amp;h=AAFdikaIBems3E9LeD0VDTwnSwxaqLF1DFWXJ3q3VzXekTsF7TE&amp;subsidiary=1&amp;vid=cai4_z7zAlRoKjQy&amp;cktime=193372&amp;redirect_count=1&amp;did_javascript_redirect=T\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">free product demo<\/a> on their website.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><b>It allows you to plug in new modules when needed, including:<\/b><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>NetSuite Financial Management 